<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-21T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="651" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6461 Tsana Dam/377:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt (<persName type="from">Jardine</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-21T11:00:00+02:00">January 21, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received January 21—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3. Following telegram has been sent by me to Southard.</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“British plan to have Egyptians pay the entire cost Tsana
                                    initially has raised storm of protest following public
                                    disclosures regarding plans and these have now been abandoned in
                                    favor of a request to the Emperor for permission for a further
                                    survey and report by the White Company. Lardner agreeable to
                                    this and is bringing under seal for your information copy of a
                                    detailed despatch to Department<note n="22" xml:id="d651fn22">Presumably despatch No. 645 of January 20, 1933, from the
                                        Minister in Egypt; not printed.</note> regarding latest
                                    developments. Am repeating to the Department.”</p>
                            </quote>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jardine</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>